[[File:Staffelegg2.jpg|thumb|]]
The '''Aargau Jura Park''' is located north of [[Aarau]], between the rivers Aare and Rhine, in the [[cantons of Switzerland|Swiss canton]] of [[Aargau]]. It straddles the border between [[canton of Jura|Jura]] and [[Basel]]. It spans {{convert|244|km2|sqmi}} and reaches up to {{convert|350|m}} above the valley floor.<ref name="spn">{{cite web|title=Portrait: Jurapark Aargau|url=http://www.paerke.ch/en/pdf/portrait/aktuell/jurapark_portrt_en.pdf|publisher=Swiss Parks Network|accessdate=1 June 2013}}</ref> The park is mainly located on the Jurassic Plateau, between [[Frick, Aargau|Frick]] and [[Villigen]], and also encompasses the Aargau Jura mountains and valleys. The northern area includes sparse pine forests, fruit orchards, rocky steppes, dry meadows and terraced vineyards, while the southern region fosters forests and wildlife.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aargau Jura Park|url=http://www.myswitzerland.com/en/the-aargau-jura.html|publisher=MySwitzerland|accessdate=1 June 2013}}</ref> It was declared a regional nature park of national importance in 2012 by the [[Federal Office for the Environment]].
The villages Herznach and Wölfinswil traditionally mined ore in the park and thus, left many studs. A mining tunnel was excavated and made accessible to visitors.
