{{About|Aberdeen Falls, a waterfall in Sri Lanka|other uses of Aberdeen|Aberdeen (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Aberdeen Falls | photo = | photo_width = | photo_caption = | map = Sri Lanka | map_width = | coordinates = {{coord|06|56|54|N|80|30|07|E|type:waterbody_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | location = [[Ginigathena]], [[Sri Lanka]] | type = Horsetail | elevation = | height = {{Convert|98|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | height_longest = | number_drops = 1 | width = {{Convert|8|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | average_width = | watercourse = [[Kehelgamu Oya]] | average_flow = | world_rank = }}
'''Aberdeen Falls''' is a {{Convert|98|m|ft|abbr=on}} high [[waterfall]] on the [[Kehelgamu Oya]] near [[Ginigathena]], in the [[Nuwara Eliya District]] of [[Sri Lanka]]. Aberdeen is named after [[Aberdeen]], the third largest city in [[Scotland]] and the capital of [[Aberdeenshire]]. [[Kehelgamu Oya]] is a major tributary of the [[Kelani River]].
To reach Aberdeen Falls from Ginigathena town, one then must proceed along Ambatale Road up to the Buddha statue at the end of the road. Then one should park their vehicle and walk about 1.2&nbsp;km along the road. Bathing in the middle of the pool and swimming to the middle has caused death to swimmers in the past. This waterfall is covered with a big stone complex behind. The waterfall is ranked as the [[List of waterfalls in Sri Lanka|18th highest on the Island]].<ref>[[#Sena04|Senanayake 2004]]: 1</ref> {{Clear}}
