'''Aces''' ({{lang-grc|Ἄκης}}), is a river of Asia, flowing through a plain surrounded by mountains, respecting which a story is told by [[Herodotus]].<ref>{{Cite Herodotus|3.117.}}</ref> Geographers are not agreed as to the locality. It seems to be somewhere in Central Asia, east of the Caspian. It is pretty clear, at all events, that the Aces of Herodotus is not the Indian river [[Acesines]] (modern Chenab).

