'''ISO 3166-2:KY''' is the entry for the [[Cayman Islands]] in [[ISO 3166-2]], part of the [[ISO 3166]] [[standardization|standard]] published by the [[International Organization for Standardization]] (ISO), which defines [[code]]s for the names of the principal [[country subdivision|subdivision]]s (e.g., [[province]]s or [[state (administrative division)|state]]s) of all [[country|countries]] coded in [[ISO 3166-1]].
Currently no second level ISO 3166-2 codes are defined in the entry for the Cayman Islands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iso.org/obp/ui/#iso:code:3166:KY|title=ISO Online Browsing Platform: KY|publisher=International Organization for Standardization (ISO)}}</ref>
The Cayman Islands are officially assigned the [[ISO 3166-1 alpha-2]] code {{mono|KY}}.
This two character string is most commonly associated with the Cayman Island's official internet domain name extension [[.ky]]
