{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Philippi Glacier | other_name = | photo = Antarctica-east2-en.jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Kaiser Wilhelm II Land | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Philippi Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = channell | location = [[Kaiser Wilhelm II Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|66|45|S|88|20|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|15|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[West Ice Shelf]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Philippi Glacier''' ({{lang-de|Philippigletscher}}) is coastal [[glacier]] about 15&nbsp;mi long, flowing N to the E end of the [[West Ice Shelf]], 15&nbsp;mi W of [[Gaussberg]]. Delineated from aerial photographs taken by U.S. Navy (USN) [[OpHjp]], 1946-47. Named by the ANCA for [[Emil Philippi]], geologist with the German Antarctic Expedition (GerAE) under [[Erich von Drygalski]], 1901–03, who made scientific observations in the vicinity of Gaussberg.
